text: Pei Chi Juan (born 10 August 1983) is a Taiwanese volleyball player. She played for the Chinese Taipei women's national volleyball team. She played at the 2006 FIVB Volleyball Women's World Championship and 2006 Asian Games. She played for National Taipei University of Education's women's volleyball team. == References == Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:Taiwanese volleyball players
